# Node.js PATH workaround (temporary)

Node.js is installed at `C:\Program Files\nodejs\node.exe` (v24.x) but is **not** on the system/user PATH yet. The user will apply a permanent PATH fix later when admin access is available.

**Before any terminal command that needs Node, npm, or Shopify CLI**, prefix the command with:

```powershell
$env:PATH += ";C:\Program Files\nodejs"
```

Or run that line once at the start of each new shell session in this workspace.

Do not assume `node`, `npm`, or `shopify` work without this prefix in a fresh terminal.
